               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240603-50-person466">
                  JOHN 
                  WILLIAMS
               <interp inst="t18240603-50-person466" type="surname" value="WILLIAMS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-50-person466" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-50-person466" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 11th of May I was working in <placeName id="t18240603-50-crimeloc262">Eagle-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18240603-50-crimeloc262" type="placeName" value="Eagle-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18240603-50-crimeloc262" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240603-50-off260 t18240603-50-crimeloc262"></join>, and went to dine at the nearest public-house at twelve o'clock - somebody came to me, and I went to the shop - the constable was there, and had a<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182406030019"></xptr>long plane of mine - I went to Hatton-garden Office, and saw the prisoner with a coat of mine, which had been left in the house in Eagle-street - I missed a square, and told the constable - we went to the lock up-house, and found it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240603-50-person467">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HANKEY
               <interp inst="t18240603-50-person467" type="surname" value="HANKEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-50-person467" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-50-person467" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a carpenter - I live at No. 7, Eagle-street - the prosecutor was in my service. On the 11th of May I saw the prisoner with these articles - I followed him, and at the end of Leigh-street I quickened my pace, and he went at full speed - I called out Stop him! and he dropped the plane, which I took up, and returned to the shop - I left the constable pursuing him, and turned round afterwards, and saw the constable collar him.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Had you ever seen him before - A. I think I have, but am not certain - I saw his side face - he was pursued by a great number people - I am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240603-50-person468">
                  EDWARD 
                  COOK
               <interp inst="t18240603-50-person468" type="surname" value="COOK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-50-person468" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-50-person468" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable - I was on duty, and saw Hankey pursuing the prisoner, who dropt the plane - I followed him, and at the corner of Princes-street he was stopped - I took him to the watch-house - I searched the watch-house about two hours afterwards, and found a small square - I had lost sight of him at some of the turnings.</p>

               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
